# gen34: conjunctive membership -- multi-fact AND, the smallest multi-hop step
# (MultiRC family). Each conjunct goes through kb_query, so rule-derived
# membership counts just like a single query; no new solver. Held-out predicates,
# and the facts arrive via the gen32 reader to keep the whole stack exercised.
> read: socrates is a man. plato is a man. every man is a mortal. zeus is a god.
< Learned 4 fact(s), skipped 0.
# Both subjects are mortal -- via the rule, not a stored fact.
> are socrates and plato both a mortal?
< Yes.
# Two classes of one subject, both holding (one direct, one rule-derived).
> is socrates both a man and a mortal?
< Yes.
# One conjunct fails -> the whole AND is no (zeus is not mortal).
> are socrates and zeus both a mortal?
< No.
> is zeus both a god and a mortal?
< No.
# An unknown class is admitted, not guessed.
> are socrates and plato both a dragon?
< I don't know about dragon.